\subsection{Variable ordering}
For the \rulename{var-swap} rule we need a stable (under $\alpha$-conversion) order of variables.
At a subexpression, one variable is considered ``less than'' another variable if
\begin{itemize}
\item Both variables bound: the variable with closest binder is considered lesser.
\item Both variables unbound: use alphabetic comparison of the variable names.
\item Otherwise, the bound variable is considered lesser.
\end{itemize}

